# whatIdid — Cursor Rules
# See .github/PLAN.md for the master implementation plan.

You are working on **whatIdid**, a personal task tracker and AI-powered notes system.

## Tech Stack
- TypeScript (strict), React 19, TanStack Start (full-stack framework)
- TanStack Router (file-based routes), TanStack React Query, TanStack React Form
- Drizzle ORM + SQLite (migrating from json-server)
- Tailwind CSS 4, tailwind-variants, Radix UI (headless UI primitives), dnd-kit
- Vitest, React Testing Library, MSW
- ESLint, Prettier, Vite
- AI: provider-agnostic abstraction (OpenAI default)

## Architecture Rules
- All data access goes through TanStack Start server functions (`createServerFn`) → Drizzle ORM → SQLite
- Never import database code in client components
- Server functions validate input with Zod schemas
- React Query manages all client-side data state (queries, mutations, optimistic updates)
- Route loaders pre-fetch data via `ensureQueryData` with React Query options
- Components consume data via `useQuery` / `useSuspenseQuery`
- Mutations use optimistic updates: cancel in-flight queries → update cache → revalidate on settle
- Feature modules live in `src/features/{domain}/` with: types.ts, server.ts, queries.ts, mutations.ts, consts.ts

## Server Functions Pattern
```typescript
export const myFunction = createServerFn({ method: 'GET' })
  .inputValidator(z.object({ /* zod schema */ }))
  .handler(async ({ data }) => {
    // Direct database access via Drizzle — no HTTP calls
    return db.select().from(table).where(eq(table.id, data.id))
  })
```

## Database Pattern (Drizzle + SQLite)
- Schema defined in `src/db/schema.ts`
- Drizzle client singleton in `src/db/index.ts`
- Migrations managed via `drizzle-kit` (`pnpm db:generate`, `pnpm db:migrate`)
- All tables include `userId` column (multi-user ready, hardcoded '1' for now)

## Code Style
- 2 spaces, single quotes, no semicolons
- Prefer `const` and `let` over `var`
- Arrow functions, named exports, no default exports
- PascalCase for components/types, camelCase for functions/variables
- Early returns for guard clauses
- Multiple components per file are fine for local/helper components; extract when reused
- One server function group per feature domain

## Styling & Design Tokens
- Tailwind CSS only — no inline styles
- `tailwind-variants` for component variants, `cn`/`twMerge` for composition
- Dark mode via `.dark` class, OKLCH color theming
- Mobile-first responsive design
- All colors, spacing, typography, and elevation use CSS custom property design tokens from `src/styles/tokens/`
- Token layers: primitives (raw palette) → semantic (role-based) → component (optional)
- Never hardcode color values — always use semantic token classes (`bg-background`, `text-foreground`, etc.)
- New themes = new CSS selector remapping semantic tokens to different primitives

## Patterns
- Query keys: `{ all: [domain], byId: [domain, id] }`
- Optimistic updates: cancel queries → update cache → revalidate on settle
- Server functions: `createServerFn({ method }) → .inputValidator(zod) → .handler()`
- Database: all tables have `userId` column (hardcode '1' for now)
- Drag-and-drop: dnd-kit with `useSortable` per item
- Components that need hydration-awareness use `useEffect` state guard

## File Organization
- `src/features/{domain}/` — feature modules (tasks, lists, categories, tags, notes, ai)
- `src/components/` — shared components, `src/components/ui/` — primitives
- `src/routes/` — file-based routes (TanStack Router)
- `src/db/` — schema, client, seeds, migrations
- `src/config/` — env vars (server/client split)
- `src/styles/` — global CSS, design tokens, theming
- `src/tests/` — test setup and mocks
- `src/utils/`, `src/hooks/` — shared utilities
- `public/` — static assets

## Testing
- Unit/Integration: Vitest + React Testing Library, MSW for mocking
- E2E: Playwright (Chromium, Firefox, WebKit) — tests in `e2e/`
- Run: `pnpm test` (unit), `pnpm test:e2e` (E2E), `pnpm test:e2e:ui` (interactive)
- No `.only` in tests
- Test server functions by mocking Drizzle client
- Dev container (`.devcontainer/`) has Playwright browsers pre-installed

## Environment & Configuration
- Use `.env.local` for local environment variables
- Never commit secrets or credentials (especially AI API keys)
- Server-only env vars in `src/config/env.server.ts` (throws if accessed client-side)
- Client env vars in `src/config/env.client.ts`
